## Scenario 3: Cross-Account S3 Access (STS AssumeRole)

**Use Case**: Trusted partner needs temporary access to specific S3 data

**Step 1: Trust Relationship (on target account's role)**
```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::987654321098:role/partner-application-role"
      },
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole",
      "Condition": {
        "StringEquals": {
          "sts:ExternalId": "unique-external-id-12345"
        },
        "IpAddress": {
          "aws:SourceIp": "203.0.113.0/24"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**Step 2: S3 Permissions (for partner's role)**
```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "AllowCrossAccountRead",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObject",
        "s3:ListBucket"
      ],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::partner-data-bucket",
        "arn:aws:s3:::partner-data-bucket/partner-access/*"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

