## Scenario 7: Compliance Officer Audit Access

**Use Case**: Compliance officer can read encryption status and logs, but not modify

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "AllowAuditRead",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:ListAllMyBuckets",
        "s3:GetBucketLocation",
        "s3:GetBucketVersioning",
        "s3:GetBucketEncryption",
        "s3:GetBucketPolicy",
        "s3:GetBucketAcl",
        "s3:GetBucketLogging",
        "s3:GetBucketPublicAccessBlock",
        "s3:ListBucket"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    },
    {
      "Sid": "AllowLogFileAccess",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObject"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::audit-logs-bucket/*"
    },
    {
      "Sid": "DenyAllModifications",
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Action": [
        "s3:PutObject",
        "s3:DeleteObject",
        "s3:PutBucketPolicy",
        "s3:PutBucketEncryption",
        "s3:PutBucketLogging"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}
```

