## Policy Testing Checklist

When implementing any of the above policies, verify:

- [ ] Policy allows required actions only
- [ ] Policy uses specific resource ARNs (not wildcards)
- [ ] Encryption is enforced (if handling sensitive data)
- [ ] Delete operations are explicitly denied where unnecessary
- [ ] Conditions restrict by VPC, IP, or time if appropriate
- [ ] Policy has been tested in non-production first
- [ ] Least privilege principle applied (explicit deny takes precedence)
- [ ] CloudTrail logs all S3 API calls
- [ ] Access reviewed quarterly
- [ ] Unused permissions removed immediately

---

## AWS CLI Implementation Examples

### Apply a policy to a role:
```bash
aws iam put-role-policy \
  --role-name my-app-role \
  --policy-name s3-access-policy \
  --policy-document file://scenario-1.json
```

### Validate policy syntax:
```bash
aws iam simulate-principal-policy \
  --policy-source-arn arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/my-app-role \
  --action-names s3:GetObject s3:PutObject \
  --resource-arns arn:aws:s3:::my-bucket/*
```

### List policies for a role:
```bash
aws iam list-role-policies \
  --role-name my-app-role
```

### Review permission:
```bash
aws iam get-role-policy \
  --role-name my-app-role \
  --policy-name s3-access-policy
```

